# Writing unit tests:
1. Never use float64, even for gradchecks as our library does not support float64.
2. If there are edge cases in the core functionality that is caught by unit tests, discuss with user
on how to proceed. Do not skip tests.

# Running Coverage:

Checking coverage for specific files/modules is not supported due to
existing bug: https://github.com/coveragepy/coveragepy/issues/1925

Instead use coverage. For e.g., to get coverage on _src:

1. coverage run --source curobo/_src/ -m pytest curobo/test/_src
2. coverage report -m


